{"parse":{"title":"Amalion","pageid":51115077,"revid":832668998,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Amalion</b> is a multilingual independent <a href=\"/wiki/Academic_publishing\" title=\"Academic publishing\">academic publishing</a> house based in <a href=\"/wiki/Dakar\" title=\"Dakar\">Dakar</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Senegal\" title=\"Senegal\">Senegal</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Amalion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Amalion is an independent pan-African publishing house based in Dakar, created in 2009.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Amalion publishes scholarly knowledge from various parts of Africa, and across linguistic boundaries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Amalion\u2019s logo is represented by the head of a lion in a plethora of colors representing the diversity of the African continent.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The first book released by Amalion in June 2009 is a collection of poetry from the Ugandan writer <a href=\"/wiki/Mildred_Kiconco_Barya\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mildred Kiconco Barya\">Mildred Kiconco Barya</a> entitled <i>Give Me Room To Move My Feet</i>. Since then, the house has published other works, including <i>A History of the <a href=\"/wiki/Yoruba_people\" title=\"Yoruba people\">Yoruba</a> People</i> by <a href=\"/wiki/Stephen_Adebanji_Akintoye\" title=\"Stephen Adebanji Akintoye\">Stephen Adebanji Akintoye</a> (2010),<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <i>La dette odieuse de l\u2019Afrique</i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> by <a href=\"/wiki/Leonce_Ndikumana\" title=\"Leonce Ndikumana\">L\u00e9once Ndikumana</a> and James Boyce (2013) on the links between debt, capital flight and development in Africa; <i>Wala Bok: Une histoire orale du hip hop au S\u00e9n\u00e9gal</i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> (2015) by Fatou Kand\u00e9 Senghor on the evolution of rap and the emergence of youth activism in Senegal <sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> and <i>My Life Has a Price</i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> by Tina Okpara (2012), a searing story of freedom from modern slavery.<sup id=\"cite_ref-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\nAmalion also published <i>The Promise of Hope</i> (2014), the last work of the Ghanaian poet <a href=\"/wiki/Kofi_Awoonor\" title=\"Kofi Awoonor\">Kofi Awoonor</a>, who died in the terrorist attack on <a href=\"/wiki/Westgate_shopping_mall_attack\" title=\"Westgate shopping mall attack\">Westgate shopping mall in Nairobi</a> in 2013, within the <i>African Poetry Book Series</i> project coordinated by the poet <a href=\"/wiki/Kwame_Dawes\" title=\"Kwame Dawes\">Kwame Dawes</a>. In 2016, the work of the renowned Nigerian historian Mahmud Modibbo Tukur <i>British colonisation of <a href=\"/wiki/Northern_Nigeria\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Northern Nigeria\">Northern Nigeria</a>, 1897-1914</i> is released. Amalion is also involved with Jacana Literary Foundation and some publishing houses around Africa in the creation of the new Gerald Kraak Award and Anthology for the promotion of gender and human rights launched in 2016.<sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Amalion titles cover literary fiction, social sciences, development studies, biographies, arts and politics aimed for academics and the general public.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Published_authors\">Published authors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Amalion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Published authors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Mildred_Kiconco_Barya\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mildred Kiconco Barya\">Mildred Kiconco Barya</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Louis_Camara\" title=\"Louis Camara\">Louis Camara</a></li>\n<li>Tina Okpara</li>\n<li>Ibrahima Amadou Niang</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Kofi_Awoonor\" title=\"Kofi Awoonor\">Kofi Awoonor</a></li>\n<li>Clifton Gachagua</li>\n<li>Kevin Eze</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Stephen_Adebanji_Akintoye\" title=\"Stephen Adebanji Akintoye\">Stephen Adebanji Akintoye</a></li>\n<li>Anthonia Makwemoisa</li>\n<li>Enyinna Chuta</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Leonce_Ndikumana\" title=\"Leonce Ndikumana\">L\u00e9once Ndikumana</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_K._Boyce\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"fr:James K. Boyce\">fr:James K. Boyce</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean-Bernard_Ou%C3%A9draogo\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"fr:Jean-Bernard Ou\u00e9draogo\">fr:Jean-Bernard Ou\u00e9draogo</a></li>\n<li>Rotimi Williams Olatunji</li>\n<li>Beatrice Adeyinka Laninhun</li>\n<li>Tope Omoniyi</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fatou_Kande_Senghor\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"fr:Fatou Kande Senghor\">fr:Fatou Kande Senghor</a></li>\n<li>Mahmud Modibbo Tukur</li>\n<li>Tade Akin Aina</li>\n<li>Bhekinkosi Moyo</li>\n<li>Fabrizio Terenzio</li>\n<li>Antoinette Tidjani Alou</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Amalion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.africultures.com/php/index.php?nav=structure&amp;no=5011&amp;texte_recherche=amalion\">\"Structures - Africultures\"</a>. <i>Africultures.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 December</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Africultures.com&amp;rft.atitle=Structures+-+Africultures&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.africultures.com%2Fphp%2Findex.php%3Fnav%3Dstructure%26no%3D5011%26texte_recherche%3Damalion&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAmalion\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Francographies, Association. <a rel=\"nofoll